class WeatherSimulator {
  private int temperature;
  private boolean isRaining;

  public WeatherSimulator(int temp, boolean rain) {
    temperature = temp;
    isRaining = rain;
  }

  public void setTemperature(int temp) {
    temperature = temp;
  }

  public void setRaining(boolean rain) {
    isRaining = rain;
  }

  public boolean increaseClouds() {
    if (temperature < 20) {
      isRaining = true;
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }

  public boolean checkFloodRisk() {
    if (isRaining && temperature < 15) {
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }
}",

If it is observed that there is a flood risk, can we intervene and deduce that isRaining was set to true?
